# AI Guidelines

Guidelines for AI agents working in this repository. The agent pipeline lives in `.claude/agents/`; the orchestrator sequences it. Process docs live in the sibling `<PROJECT>-OPS` repo, not in this codebase.

## Source of truth

- **Code + conventional READMEs** live in this repo.
- **All process docs** (PRDs, research, implementation plans, handover summaries) live in the sibling **`<PROJECT>-OPS`** repo.
- **`<PROJECT>-OPS/INDEX.md`** is the doc registry and the orchestrator's context wiki — **read it first** to locate any doc; never sweep the tree.
- Issue tracking and review happen on **GitHub** (Issues + Pull Requests). Reference the issue (`#NNN`) in commit bodies and PR descriptions.

## AI-Specific Git Workflow Rules

**CRITICAL: AI assistants MUST follow these rules for any code change:**

1. **NEVER commit directly to the integration branch** (default `main`; some repos use `develop`/`rdev`). All commits go to a feature branch. If you're not on one, create it first.
2. **One topic per feature branch.** Do not mix unrelated changes. Naming: `feature/<slug>`, `fix/<slug>`, `docs/<slug>`, `refactor/<slug>`, `test/<slug>`, `chore/<slug>`.
3. **Separate concerns into different branches** — infra, docs, fixes, and features each get their own branch.
4. **Before changing anything, verify the current branch** with `git status`. If on the integration branch, branch off immediately.
5. **Commit message format:** conventional commits — `type(scope): description`. Reference the GitHub issue in the body.
6. **When switching topics, switch branches.** Commit/push current work first.

## Standard Workflow

```bash
git checkout <integration-branch>      # default main
git pull
git checkout -b feature/descriptive-name
# make focused changes
git add <files>
git commit -m "feat(scope): description"   # body: closes #NNN
git push -u origin feature/descriptive-name
gh pr create --base <integration-branch>   # open PR; do not merge your own
```

Do not merge your own PRs — the pipeline's `pr-reviewer` gate and the user's approval come first.

## Handover discipline

Every agent run writes a handover summary to `<PROJECT>-OPS/comms/YYYY-MM-DD-<agent>-<scope>.md`, and registers any doc it produces in `<PROJECT>-OPS/INDEX.md`. See `.claude/agents/orchestrator.md` for the full gate sequence.

## Questions?

If a guideline is unclear, ask the user before proceeding. Do not invent process — mirror what the repo already does.
